    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-08-04T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-08-04T04:00:00-05:00" n="172"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d172">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11057: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-08-04T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 4, 1930—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 4—8:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>667. Legation’s 659, August 3, 11 a.m.<note n="73" xml:id="d172fn73">Not
                        printed.</note> Following from <hi rend="italic">Palos</hi> at Changsha,
                    August 4th: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Informed reliably about five thousand Ho Chien troops at Yolanshan west
                            of west side of island. Also few Communists remaining Changsha. Appears
                            Ho Chien and Fifty-third Division, that apparently armed in part, may
                            make effort retake Changsha today or tomorrow. Learned all Communists
                            evacuated city when <hi rend="italic">Palos</hi> forced to return fire
                            the other day and only handful returned. Have received contact
                            information of Ho Chien army. Will remain opposite Socony till city safe
                            to return, avoiding take any part recapture city, moral or
                            otherwise.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
